quran[21]{c,v,t}:
  6,74,"And ňĻrememberňļ when Abraham said to his father, »āzar, ‚ÄúDo you take idols as gods? It is clear to me that you and your people are entirely misguided.‚ÄĚ"
  6,75,"We also showed Abraham the wonders of the heavens and the earth, so he would be sure in faith"
  6,76,"When the night grew dark upon him, he saw a star and said, ‚ÄúThis is my Lord!‚ÄĚ But when it set, he said, ‚ÄúI do not love things that set.‚ÄĚ"
  6,77,"Then when he saw the moon rising, he said, ‚ÄúThis one is my Lord!‚ÄĚ But when it disappeared, he said, ‚ÄúIf my Lord does not guide me, I will certainly be one of the misguided people.‚ÄĚ"
  6,78,"Then when he saw the sun shining, he said, ‚ÄúThis must be my Lord‚ÄĒit is the greatest!‚ÄĚ But again when it set, he declared, ‚ÄúO my people! I totally reject whatever you associate ňĻwith Allah in worshipňļ"
  6,79,I have turned my face towards the One Who has originated the heavens and the earth‚ÄĒbeing upright‚ÄĒand I am not one of the polytheists.‚ÄĚ
  6,80,"And his people argued with him. He responded, ‚ÄúAre you arguing with me about Allah, while He has guided me? I am not afraid of whatever ňĻidolsňļ you associate with Him‚ÄĒňĻnone can harm me,ňļ unless my Lord so wills. My Lord encompasses everything in ňĻHisňļ knowledge. Will you not be mindful"
  6,81,"And how should I fear your associate-gods, while you have no fear in associating ňĻothersňļ with Allah‚ÄĒa practice He has never authorized? Which side has more right to security? ňĻTell meňļ if you really know!‚ÄĚ"
  6,82,It is ňĻonlyňļ those who are faithful and do not tarnish their faith with falsehood¬†who are guaranteed security and are ňĻrightlyňļ guided
  6,83,"This was the argument We gave Abraham against his people. We elevate in rank whoever We please. Surely your Lord is All-Wise, All-Knowing"
  6,84,"And We blessed him with Isaac and Jacob. We guided them all as We previously guided Noah and those among his descendants: David, Solomon, Job, Joseph, Moses, and Aaron. This is how We reward the good-doers"
  6,85,"Likewise, ňĻWe guidedňļ Zachariah, John, Jesus, and Elias, who were all of the righteous"
  6,86,"ňĻWe also guidedňļ Ishmael, Elisha, Jonah, and Lot, favouring each over other people ňĻof their timeňļ"
  6,87,"And ňĻWe favouredňļ some of their forefathers, their descendants, and their brothers. We chose them and guided them to the Straight Path"
  6,88,"This is Allah‚Äôs guidance with which He guides whoever He wills of His servants. Had they associated others with Him ňĻin worshipňļ, their ňĻgoodňļ deeds would have been wasted"
  6,89,"Those were the ones to whom We gave the Scripture, wisdom, and prophethood. But if these ňĻpagansňļ disbelieve in this ňĻmessageňļ, then We have already entrusted it to a people who will never disbelieve in it"
  6,90,"These ňĻprophetsňļ were ňĻrightlyňļ guided by Allah, so follow their guidance. Say, ‚ÄúI ask no reward of you for this ňĻQuranňļ‚ÄĒit is a reminder to the whole world.‚ÄĚ"
  6,91,"And they¬†have not shown Allah His proper reverence when they said, ‚ÄúAllah has revealed nothing to any human being.‚ÄĚ Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúWho then revealed the Book brought forth by Moses as a light and guidance for people, which you split into separate sheets‚ÄĒrevealing some and hiding much? You have been taught ňĻthrough this Quranňļ what neither you nor your forefathers knew.‚ÄĚ Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúAllah ňĻrevealed itňļ!‚ÄĚ Then leave them to amuse themselves with falsehood"
  6,92,This is a blessed Book which We have revealed‚ÄĒconfirming what came before it‚ÄĒso you may warn the Mother of Cities¬†and everyone around it. Those who believe in the Hereafter ňĻtrulyňļ believe in it and guard their prayers
  6,93,"Who does more wrong than the one who fabricates lies against Allah or claims, ‚ÄúI have received revelations!‚ÄĚ‚ÄĒalthough nothing was revealed to them‚ÄĒor the one who says, ‚ÄúI can reveal the like of Allah‚Äôs revelations!‚ÄĚ? If you ňĻO Prophetňļ could only see the wrongdoers in the throes of death while the angels are stretching out their hands ňĻsayingňļ, ‚ÄúGive up your souls! Today you will be rewarded with the torment of disgrace for telling lies about Allah and for being arrogant towards His revelations!‚ÄĚ"
  6,94,ňĻTodayňļ you have come back to Us all alone as We created you the first time‚ÄĒleaving behind everything We have provided you with. We do not see your intercessors with you‚ÄĒthose you claimed were Allah‚Äôs partners ňĻin worshipňļ. All your ties have been broken and all your claims have let you down.‚ÄĚ